'''Ōtokoro Shrine''' (おおところじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Morinishi, {{ill|lt=Makino-chō|Q6739696|WD=Q6739696|1=Makino, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Takashima, Shiga|Q845794|WD=Q845794|1=Takashima, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}, and its {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=former shrine rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|WD=Q712534}} was {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deity ===
*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōtojinushi-no-Kami|1=UNKNOWN}}

=== History ===
It is said to have been founded in 670 (9th year of {{ill|lt=Emperor Tenji|Q314802|WD=Q314802|1=Emperor Tenji}}), and is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}<ref name="巨樹と花">[http://www.tree-flower.jp/25/ootokoro_jinja_1103/ootokoro_katsura.html 大處神社のカツラ - 巨樹と花のページ] Accessed February 26, 2019</ref>. According to shrine tradition, because white boar, white horse, and white chicken were offered in this shrine land and nearby area to worship Toshigami, there was a rite of offering boar at the Kinensai festival. The Mine-mori family served as the shrine household, and it was the sōsha of Ōtokoro-go, one of the ten villages of Takashima District.

